    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a high-floor offensive projection anchored by two elite plays. **Trea Turner** (81.27) and **Kyle Schwarber** (79.42) represent our strongest daily assets, both benefiting from a favorable matchup against Mart\u00edn P\u00e9rez. With an xERA of 4.78, P\u00e9rez provides a significant SP skill advantage, and when paired with **Trea Turner**\u2019s optimal leadoff positioning (+10% order bonus) and **Kyle Schwarber**\u2019s elite xwOBA of 0.402, both are locked in as high-efficiency starts. Furthermore, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (73.14) and **Hyeseong Kim** (70.16) offer significant upside despite their lower batting order, as both leverage favorable platoon dynamics and park factors that elevate their production well above their base projections.\n\nThe most difficult decision today involved the final roster spot, with **Victor Scott II** (47.57) ultimately falling just shy of the cutoff. While **Victor Scott II**\u2019s elite speed is a premium asset for our category scarcity strategy, the optimizer prioritized the higher floor and superior park/platoon integration offered by players like **Carson Benge** and **Jerar Encarnacion**. **Colt Keith** also remained on the bench due to a challenging L/L matchup against Ranger Suarez, which suppressed his efficiency score below the 50-point threshold. We remain cautious regarding **Junior Caminero** (53.51); while he is starting, his score is tempered by a significant -19% SP skill penalty against a high-end arm in Bubba Chandler. Monitor lineup confirmation closely, as the \"Lineup Pending\" status for **Gary Sanchez**, **Dillon Dingler**, and **Kazuma Okamoto** introduces volatility should these players be shuffled into defensive slots with lower offensive output expectations. **Christian Yelich** remains sidelined, continuing to limit our depth at the outfield positions.",
